<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06028200 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06028200 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  CARMEL; PROFESSIONAL; GOLF; CHAMPIONSHIP  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  (box) WHAT: A stroke-play, pro-amateur golf tournament over 72 holes startingThursday on the Monterey Peninsula.;    (box) WHERE: At the Pebble Beach,Spyglass Hill and Poppy Hills courses Thursday through Saturday, and at PebbleBeach on Sunday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  PEBBLE BEACH NATIONAL PRO-AM AT A GLANCE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Golf  </MEMO><TEXT>     (box) WHY: To raise about $1 million for California charities.;    (box) ATSTAKE: 180 professionals paired with 180 amateurs in two-man teams; pros playfor a purse of $1,170,000, with first place worth $198,000 to the individualwinner and $70,000 to the pro-am winner; amateurs play for prizes. Cut will beafter three rounds to the low 60 pros and ties and low 25 pro-am teams andties.;    (box) TEE TIMES: Competition starts at 8:30 a.m. and ends about 4p.m. the first three days. Sunday tee times to be announced. Play is infoursomes, rotating to each of the three courses. Complimentary pairing sheetsavailable at all entrances starting Thursday.;    (box) TICKETS: BASS or at17-Mile Drive entrance gates. Prices: Today through Wednesday, $10 each day;Thursday through Sunday, $20; season badge, $75.;    (box) DIRECTIONS:Admission via three gates -- Carmel, Carmel Hill, Pacific Grove. Auto gate feewaived to ticket holders.;    (box) PARKING: No charge; follow traffic-controlsigns; courtesy transportation between courses.;    (box) PROS TO WATCH:Defending champion Mark O'Meara, Jack Nicklaus, Curtis Strange, Tom Watson,Arnold Palmer, Tom Kite, Hale Irwin, Payne Stewart, Sandy Lyle, Paul Azinger,Mark Calcavecchia, Raymond Floyd, Ben Crenshaw, Fred Couples, Johnny Miller,Bob Tway, Craig Stadler, Lanny Wadkins, Fuzzy Zoeller, Peter Jacobsen, ChipBeck, Larry Mize, Mark Wiebe, Roger Maltbie, Steve Jones and Davis Love III.;   (box) CELEBRITIES INCLUDE: Jack Lemmon, Clint Eastwood, Huey Lewis, MichaelTucker, Don Johnson, John Elway, Steve Young, Frank Viola, Dave Righetti,Gatlin Brothers (Larry, Rudy, Steve), Randy Cross, Julius Erving, OrelHershiser, Alan Shepard, Mark McGwire, Willie McCovey, Bob Lurie, BretSaberhagen, Tommy Smothers, Ed Marinaro, Jack Wagner, James Garner and CharlesSchulz.;    (box) DAY BY DAY: Today -- Practice rounds. Tuesday -- Practicerounds; 2 p.m. -- Pro shootout over nine holes at Pebble Beach featuringO'Meara, Beck, Crenshaw, Zoeller, Mize, Love, Irwin, Azinger, Couples andSteve Elkington. Wednesday -- Practice rounds; 11 a.m. -- Celebrity shootoutover five holes at Pebble Beach featuring six players; 3:30 p.m. -- A youthclinic at Polo Field, with pros giving tips to youngsters accompanied byticket-holding adult. Thursday -- First round, three courses. Friday -- Secondround. Saturday -- Third round; Sunday -- Final round at Pebble Beach. Aplayoff, if needed, will be held immediately after Sunday play.;    (box)TELEVISION: Thursday -- USA cable, 4 p.m. Friday -- USA cable, 1-3 p.m.Saturday -- , 1-3 p.m.; Sunday -- , 1-3 p.m.;    (box) HOW TO GALLERY: Staybehind ropes at all times; follow directions of marshals; do not ask forautographs during play; cameras are permitted, but pictures must not be takenwhile players are competing.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910128  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  473  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday January 28, 199100028200,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>